rComments: Very caring, the content are not hard at all if you take the time to do it. Weekly assignments and homework make a huge part of evaluation.
She's very nice and I love her.

Relatively boring lectures but you can tell she really wants her students to succeed & put in solid effort to make stats interesting. I really appreciated how much she cared about teaching a good course. Relied heavily on the textbook but I found that beneficial for this course. Lectures were helpful if text was unclear, but not necessary.
